# No Slop UI

When building or editing frontend UI in this project, follow `vendor/no-slop-ui/SKILL.md` and `DESIGN.md`.

## Priority

1. Use existing CSS variables from `theme.css` — never replace with generic purple/blue palettes
2. Reuse existing component classes — do not invent parallel design systems
3. Read `vendor/no-slop-ui/references/banned-patterns.md` before writing UI code

## Hard bans

- Glassmorphism, gradient decoration, AI purple aesthetic
- Inter font, eyebrow labels, dashboard hero sections
- Floating metric-card grids (use flat `.kpi-row` instead)
- Pill buttons, dramatic shadows, hover transforms
- Marketing copy in internal ops pages

## Standard

Think Linear / Stripe ops console: functional, bordered, restrained. Radius stays at 2px. Borders over shadows.
